    "id": "ssc_2018_q80",
    "question": "Sudha saves 15% of her income. If her expenditure increases by 20% and savings increase by 60%, then by what percent has her income increased? 24",
    "options": {
      "A": "",
      "B": "30",
      "C": "26",
      "D": "35"
    },
    "correctAnswer": "C",
    "correctValue": "26",
    "difficulty": "easy",
    "topic": "percentage",
    "year": 2018,
    "exam": "SSC CGL",
    "explanation": "Step 1: Let expenditure = 100. Income is 20% more вЖТ income = 120. Savings = 120 вИТ 100 = 20.\nStep 2: After increases: new income = 120 √Ч 1.2 = 144, new expenditure = 100 √Ч 1.6 = 160.\nStep 3: New savings = 144 вИТ 160 = -16. Change% = (-16 вИТ 20) / 20 √Ч 100 = -180%.\nFinal Answer: 26"
  },
